cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the analysis of outage probability and transmission capacity of wireless networks, which are key topics in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on ad hoc wireless networks, which fall under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper discusses the use of multiple antennas and diversity techniques in ad hoc networks, which can be seen as a form of multiagent systems. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the performance of different transmission techniques in wireless networks, which can be viewed as a control problem. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper does not directly deal with multimedia, but the use of multiple antennas and diversity techniques can improve the quality of multimedia transmission in wireless networks.
